-- Avianca signs MOU for 51 Airbus A320-family planes
-- 
-- Wed Jun 22, 2011 6:25am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/06/22/us-airshow-avianca-airbus-idUSTRE75L1S220110622

 

 LE BOURGET, France  (Reuters) - Colombian airline Avianca signed a memorandum of understanding to purchase 18 Airbus A320 and 33 revamped A320neo aircraft at the Paris Air Show on Wednesday. 

 The A320s are worth $1.5 billion and the A320neo aircraft are worth $3 billion, based on list prices. (Reporting by Matthias Blamont; Editing by  James Regan )